# Pre-restructure fossils (root-level Python modules from before apps/ + config/
# layout). These do NOT exist in git, but they have re-appeared on the VPS host
# (/opt/labcontrol/) at least twice (2026-05-05 cleanup + 2026-05-06 redeploy).
# Dockerfile uses `COPY . .`, so without these excludes a fossil /app/celery.py
# would shadow the `celery` Python package and crash gunicorn at boot.
# Until Dockerfile is migrated to a whitelist `COPY apps/ ./apps/` style, keep
# these explicit:
/celery.py
/urls.py
/wsgi.py
/asgi.py
/admin.py
/__init__.py
